'''Ngal'ayel Mukau''' (born 3 November 2004) is a professional [[association football|football]]er who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Ligue 1]] club [[Lille OSC|Lille]]. Born in Belgium, he plays for the [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo national team]].

==Club career==
===Mechelen===
Mukau is a youth product of [[K.V. Mechelen|Mechelen]] and [[S.V. Zulte Waregem|Zulte Waregem]]. On 20 July 2022, he signed his first professional contract with Mechelen for 2+1 seasons.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gva.be/cnt/dmf20220720_95175326|title=Ngal'ayel Mukau krijgt eerste profcontract bij KV Mechelen|date=20 July 2022|website=Gazet van Antwerpen}}</ref> He made his senior and professional debut with Mechelen in a 2–0 [[Belgian First Division A]] loss to [[S.V. Zulte Waregem|Zulte Waregem]] on 8 January 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://voetbalflitsen.be/nieuws/e8v28v/wie-is-ngalayel-mukau-18-jarig-toptalent-van-kv-mechelen-dat-al-debuteerde-in-1a-dit-seizoen|title=Wie is Ngal'ayel Mukau, 18-jarig toptalent van KV Mechelen dat al debuteerde in 1A dit seizoen?|date=20 February 2023|website=Voetbalflitsen.be - het leukste en opvallendste voetbalnieuws!}}</ref>

===Lille===
On 11 July 2024, Mukau signed for French [[Ligue 1]] club [[Lille OSC|Lille]], on a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite news |language=fr |url=https://www.losc.fr/actualites/2024-07-11/le-prometteur-ngalayel-mukau-est-lillois |title=Le prometteur Ngal'ayel Mukau est Lillois |date=11 July 2024 |website=[[Lille OSC|LOSC]] |access-date=29 November 2024}}</ref> The financial details of the transfer include an initial and base fee of €4 million and a maximum of €1 million add-ons depending on sporting conditions.<ref>{{cite news |language=fr |url=https://lepetitlillois.com/2024/07/12/plus-attractif-le-losc-a-coiffe-le-club-bruges-au-poteau-pour-ngalayel-mukau |title=Plus attractif, le LOSC a coiffé le Club Bruges au poteau pour Ngal'ayel Mukau |last=Marcant |first=Raphaël |date=12 July 2024 |website=Le Petit Lillois |access-date=29 November 2024}}</ref> On 27 November, he scored his first professional goals with a brace in a 2–1 win at [[Bologna FC 1909|Bologna]] in the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League league phase]].<ref>{{cite news |language=fr |url=https://www.losc.fr/actualites/2024-11-27/bologne-losc-le-compte-rendu |title=Bologne-LOSC (1-2) : Epatants, une fois de plus ! |last=Pousset |first=Maxime |date=27 November 2024 |website=[[Lille OSC|LOSC]] |access-date=29 November 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in Belgium, Mukau is of DR Congolese descent. Mukau holds both Congolese and French nationalities from his parents. He is a former youth international for Belgium, having played for the [[Belgium national under-18 football team|Belgium U18]]s. However, he was called up to a training camp for the [[DR Congo national under-20 football team|DR Congo U21]]s in September 2023,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.leopardsfoot.com/binationaux-a-qui-le-tour/|title=Binationaux : à qui le tour ?|date=26 September 2023}}</ref> and debuted with them in a pair of friendlies against the [[Tunisia national under-20 football team|Tunisia U20]]s in October 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://foot-africa.com/fr/afrique/rd-congo/nouveau-pogba-bresil-rdc/|title=Le "nouveau Pogba" Snobe Le Brésil Et Choisit La RDC|date=5 October 2023}}</ref>

On 16 November 2024, he made his debut for the [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo national team]], coming on as a substitute in a [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualification Group H|2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualification]] against [[Guinea national football team|Guinea]].<ref>{{cite web|access-date=1 December 2024 |author=Raphael Marcant |date=17 November 2024 |title=Première sélection avec la République Démocratique du Congo pour Ngal'ayel Mukau (LOSC) |url=https://lepetitlillois.com/2024/11/17/premiere-cap-avec-la-republique-democratique-du-congo-pour-ngalayel-mukau-losc/ |website=lepetitlillois.com}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator -->.</ref>

